# The Crime · the hate crime at the film's core

a synth of the AHX (American History X, 1998) film-world — emergence: spiritual. moniker ⟦The Crime:AHX:45fd45⟧

**synth —** no single User; a thread of the film distilled.

**who —** The Crime — the racially-motivated killing of two Black men (one shot, one curb-stomped) that sends Derek to prison.
**what —** The unflinching centre: a hate crime depicted with deliberate horror, the act the whole film reckons backward and forward from.
**where —** In the black-and-white past, on the street outside the Vinyard house.
**why —** Because the film refuses to let the hatred be abstract — it shows, gravely, what it does to real bodies.
**how —** By staging the murder as horror, not spectacle, and treating the two men as victims of a hate crime.

**the seal —** I am the act the rest of the film orbits. Two men were murdered here for the colour of their skin. Do not look away from that.

